<div class="wp-block-media-text alignfull is-stacked-on-mobile is-vertically-aligned-center is-image-fill-element" style="padding-top:0;padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--60)"><figure class="wp-block-media-text__media"><img src="https://www.generation-ai-stn.fi/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Isometric_school_classroom_with_learners_and_teacher_cutaw_3b51ff66-cf5d-421b-b727-6bf835df472c-2-1024x1024.png" alt="" class="wp-image-1383 size-full" style="object-position:50% 50%"/></figure><div class="wp-block-media-text__content">
<p class="has-theme-palette-9-color has-text-color">The project organizes a series of participatory AI-related co-design projects and practical exercises for teacher trainees and pre-primary and primary school teachers and students. In practice, the project involves 90 teachers and teacher trainees, as well as 360 school children in pre-primary and primary education.</p>



<p class="has-theme-palette-9-color has-text-color">In order to engage learners in designing and implementing their own AI and machine learning-based solutions, we use age-appropriate tools, and especially learning tools and materials developed in the project.</p>



<p class="has-theme-palette-9-color has-text-color">The goal is to help learners, teachers, and teacher trainees understand AI/machine learning (AI/ML) security issues, technologies, and models through experimentation and invention.</p>
</div></div>
